{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775859025167,"sessionID":"ses_2868f772dffedk9WSHy9p19eik","part":{"id":"prt_d7970f1bd001QxKqXDamug77oj","messageID":"msg_d7970e5d7001vDIuMME4zbatxY","sessionID":"ses_2868f772dffedk9WSHy9p19eik","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_cfc62231755547b9bbb7ec41","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/picod/design.md","content":"# Design: AR-015 PicoD Command Execution API\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-015 — PicoD Command Execution API |\n| Module | `pkg/picod` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-1 completed |\n\nThis document describes the technical implementation for the PicoD command execution API within `pkg/picod`. The PicoD module provides secure, resource-limited command execution capabilities for the AgentCube platform, serving as the execution engine for code interpreters and agent runtimes.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Component Structure\n\n```\npkg/picod/\n├── picod.go                 # Main PicoD struct and initialization\n├── picod_test.go            # PicoD unit tests\n├── executor.go              # Command execution logic\n├── executor_test.go         # Execution unit tests\n├── limits.go                # Resource limit definitions and enforcement\n├── limits_test.go           # Resource limit tests\n├── security.go              # Security validation and hardening\n├── security_test.go         # Security tests\n├── output.go                # Output capture and streaming\n├── output_test.go           # Output handling tests\n├── process.go               # Running process management\n├── process_test.go          # Process management tests\n├── errors.go                # Error type definitions\n└── config.go                # Configuration from environment\n```\n\n### Integration Points\n\n- **os/exec**: Standard library command execution primitives\n- **syscall**: Process management, signals, and resource limits\n- **context**: Command cancellation and timeouts\n- **k8s.io/klog/v2**: Structured logging\n- **pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1**: Type definitions for CodeInterpreter\n- **pkg/common/types**: SandboxInfo type definitions\n\n### Execution Flow\n\n```\nClient (WorkloadManager/CodeInterpreter)\n  ↓\nPicoD.New(sandboxID, options...)\n  ↓\nPicoD.Run(ctx, Command)\n  ├─ ValidateCommand(cmd, securityOpts)\n  ├─ ApplyResourceLimits(limits)\n  ├─ exec.CommandContext(ctx, path, args...)\n  ├─ Configure cmd.SysProcAttr\n  ├─ Start process\n  ├─ Monitor with timeout/limits\n  ├─ Capture stdout/stderr\n  └─ Return CommandResult\n```\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### PicoD\n\n```go\n// PicoD represents a command execution sandbox\ntype PicoD struct {\n    sandboxID    string\n    workDir      string\n    limits       *ResourceLimits\n    securityOpts *SecurityOptions\n    logger       klog.Logger\n}\n\n// Option is a functional option for PicoD\ntype Option func(*PicoD)\n```\n\n### ResourceLimits\n\n```go\n// ResourceLimits defines execution resource limits\ntype ResourceLimits struct {\n    // Timeout is the maximum execution duration\n    Timeout time.Duration\n    \n    // MaxCPU is the maximum CPU cores (e.g., 0.5, 1.0)\n    MaxCPU float64\n    \n    // MaxMemory is the maximum memory in bytes\n    MaxMemory int64\n    \n    // MaxOutputSize is the maximum output size in bytes\n    MaxOutputSize int64\n    \n    // MaxProcesses is the maximum number of processes\n    MaxProcesses int\n}\n```\n\n### SecurityOptions\n\n```go\n// SecurityOptions defines security settings for command execution\ntype SecurityOptions struct {\n    // UID is the user ID to run commands as\n    UID int\n    \n    // GID is the group ID to run commands as\n    GID int\n    \n    // Capabilities is the list of allowed capabilities\n    Capabilities []string\n    \n    // ReadOnlyFS makes the filesystem read-only\n    ReadOnlyFS bool\n    \n    // NoNetwork disables network access\n    NoNetwork bool\n    \n    // AllowedCommands is an optional allowlist of command paths\n    AllowedCommands []string\n}\n```\n\n### Command\n\n```go\n// Command represents a command to execute\ntype Command struct {\n    // Path is the command path\n    Path string\n    \n    // Args are the command arguments\n    Args []string\n    \n    // Env is the environment variables\n    Env []string\n    \n    // Dir is the working directory\n    Dir string\n    \n    // Stdin is the standard input\n    Stdin io.Reader\n    \n    // Stdout is the standard output (optional, captured if nil)\n    Stdout io.Writer\n    \n    // Stderr is the standard error (optional, captured if nil)\n    Stderr io.Writer\n}\n```\n\n### CommandResult\n\n```go\n// CommandResult represents the result of command execution\ntype CommandResult struct {\n    // ExitCode is the process exit code\n    ExitCode int\n    \n    // Stdout is the captured standard output\n    Stdout []byte\n    \n    // Stderr is the captured standard error\n    Stderr []byte\n    \n    // Duration is the execution duration\n    Duration time.Duration\n    \n    // OOMKilled indicates if the process was killed due to OOM\n    OOMKilled bool\n    \n    // Timeout indicates if the command timed out\n    Timeout bool\n}\n```\n\n### Process\n\n```go\n// Process represents a running process\ntype Process struct {\n    // PID is the process ID\n    PID int\n    \n    // cmd is the underlying exec.Cmd\n    cmd *exec.Cmd\n    \n    // startTime is when the process started\n    startTime time.Time\n}\n```\n\n### OutputHandler\n\n```go\n// OutputHandler handles streaming output\ntype OutputHandler interface {\n    // OnStdout is called when stdout data is available\n    OnStdout(data []byte)\n    \n    // OnStderr is called when stderr data is available\n    OnStderr(data []byte)\n    \n    // OnComplete is called when execution completes\n    OnComplete(result *CommandResult)\n}\n```\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### PicoD Initialization\n\n```go\n// New creates a new PicoD instance\nfunc New(sandboxID string, opts ...Option) *PicoD\n\n// WithWorkDir sets the working directory\nfunc WithWorkDir(dir string) Option\n\n// WithLimits sets resource limits\nfunc WithLimits(limits *ResourceLimits) Option\n\n// WithSecurityOpts sets security options\nfunc WithSecurityOpts(opts *SecurityOptions) Option\n\n// WithLogger sets the logger\nfunc WithLogger(logger klog.Logger) Option\n```\n\n### Command Execution\n\n```go\n// Run executes a command and waits for completion\nfunc (p *PicoD) Run(ctx context.Context, cmd *Command) (*CommandResult, error)\n\n// Start starts a command without waiting\nfunc (p *PicoD) Start(ctx context.Context, cmd *Command) (*Process, error)\n\n// RunWithStreaming executes a command with streaming output\nfunc (p *PicoD) RunWithStreaming(ctx context.Context, cmd *Command, handler OutputHandler) (*CommandResult, error)\n```\n\n### Process Management\n\n```go\n// Wait waits for the process to complete\nfunc (p *Process) Wait() (*CommandResult, error)\n\n// Kill sends a signal to the process\nfunc (p *Process) Kill(signal os.Signal) error\n\n// Signal sends a specific signal to the process\nfunc (p *Process) Signal(sig syscall.Signal) error\n```\n\n### Resource Limits\n\n```go\n// DefaultResourceLimits returns default resource limits\nfunc DefaultResourceLimits() *ResourceLimits\n\n// Validate validates resource limits\nfunc (l *ResourceLimits) Validate() error\n\n// Apply applies resource limits to a process\nfunc (l *ResourceLimits) Apply(cmd *exec.Cmd) error\n```\n\n### Security Validation\n\n```go\n// DefaultSecurityOpts returns default security options\nfunc DefaultSecurityOpts() *SecurityOptions\n\n// Validate validates security options\nfunc (o *SecurityOptions) Validate() error\n\n// ValidateCommand validates a command for security\nfunc ValidateCommand(cmd *Command, opts *SecurityOptions) error\n\n// IsPathSafe checks if a path is within the allowed workspace\nfunc IsPathSafe(path, workDir string) bool\n```\n\n### Configuration\n\n```go\n// LoadConfig loads configuration from environment variables\nfunc LoadConfig() (*Config, error)\n\n// Config holds PicoD configuration\ntype Config struct {\n    WorkDir         string\n    DefaultTimeout  time.Duration\n    MaxMemory       int64\n    MaxCPU          float64\n    MaxOutputSize   int64\n    MaxProcesses    int\n}\n```\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### ExecutionError\n\n```go\n// ExecutionError represents an execution error\ntype ExecutionError struct {\n    // Type is the error type\n    Type ExecutionErrorType\n    \n    // Message is the error message\n    Message string\n    \n    // Underlying is the underlying error\n    Underlying error\n}\n\n// Error implements the error interface\nfunc (e *ExecutionError) Error() string\n\n// Unwrap returns the underlying error\nfunc (e *ExecutionError) Unwrap() error\n```\n\n### ExecutionErrorType\n\n```go\ntype ExecutionErrorType string\n\nconst (\n    ExecutionErrorTimeout    ExecutionErrorType = \"timeout\"\n    ExecutionErrorOOM        ExecutionErrorType = \"oom\"\n    ExecutionErrorCancelled  ExecutionErrorType = \"cancelled\"\n    ExecutionErrorSecurity   ExecutionErrorType = \"security\"\n    ExecutionErrorResource   ExecutionErrorType = \"resource\"\n    ExecutionErrorExec       ExecutionErrorType = \"exec\"\n)\n```\n\n### Error Conditions\n\n| Condition | Error Type | HTTP Mapping | Description |\n|-----------|------------|--------------|-------------|\n| Command exceeds timeout | `ExecutionErrorTimeout` | 408 Request Timeout | Command execution exceeded configured timeout |\n| Command exceeds memory | `ExecutionErrorOOM` | 413 Payload Too Large | Process was killed due to OOM |\n| Context cancelled | `ExecutionErrorCancelled` | 499 Client Closed Request | Client cancelled the operation |\n| Security violation | `ExecutionErrorSecurity` | 403 Forbidden | Command failed security validation |\n| Resource limit invalid | `ExecutionErrorResource` | 400 Bad Request | Invalid resource limit configuration |\n| Exec failure | `ExecutionErrorExec` | 500 Internal Server Error | Failed to start/execute command |\n\n## Implementation Details\n\n### PicoD Initialization\n\n```go\nfunc New(sandboxID string, opts ...Option) *PicoD {\n    p := &PicoD{\n        sandboxID:    sandboxID,\n        workDir:      \"/tmp/picod/\" + sandboxID,\n        limits:       DefaultResourceLimits(),\n        securityOpts: DefaultSecurityOpts(),\n        logger:       klog.Background(),\n    }\n    \n    for _, opt := range opts {\n        opt(p)\n    }\n    \n    return p\n}\n```\n\n### Command Execution Flow\n\n```go\nfunc (p *PicoD) Run(ctx context.Context, cmd *Command) (*CommandResult, error) {\n    // 1. Validate command\n    if err := ValidateCommand(cmd, p.securityOpts); err != nil {\n        return nil, &ExecutionError{\n            Type:    ExecutionErrorSecurity,\n            Message: \"command validation failed\",\n            Underlying: err,\n        }\n    }\n    \n    // 2. Create exec.Cmd\n    execCmd := exec.CommandContext(ctx, cmd.Path, cmd.Args...)\n    \n    // 3. Configure environment\n    execCmd.Env = cmd.Env\n    execCmd.Dir = cmd.Dir\n    \n    // 4. Apply resource limits\n    if err := p.limits.Apply(execCmd); err != nil {\n        return nil, &ExecutionError{\n            Type:    ExecutionErrorResource,\n            Message: \"failed to apply resource limits\",\n            Underlying: err,\n        }\n    }\n    \n    // 5. Capture output\n    var stdoutBuf, stderrBuf bytes.Buffer\n    if cmd.Stdout == nil {\n        execCmd.Stdout = &stdoutBuf\n    } else {\n        execCmd.Stdout = cmd.Stdout\n    }\n    if cmd.Stderr == nil {\n        execCmd.Stderr = &stderrBuf\n    } else {\n        execCmd.Stderr = cmd.Stderr\n    }\n    \n    // 6. Start execution\n    startTime := time.Now()\n    if err := execCmd.Start(); err != nil {\n        return nil, &ExecutionError{\n            Type:    ExecutionErrorExec,\n            Message: \"failed to start command\",\n            Underlying: err,\n        }\n    }\n    \n    // 7. Wait for completion\n    err := execCmd.Wait()\n    duration := time.Since(startTime)\n    \n    // 8. Build result\n    result := &CommandResult{\n        Duration: duration,\n    }\n    \n    if cmd.Stdout == nil {\n        result.Stdout = stdoutBuf.Bytes()\n    }\n    if cmd.Stderr == nil {\n        result.Stderr = stderrBuf.Bytes()\n    }\n    \n    // 9. Check for timeout/OOM\n    if ctx.Err() == context.DeadlineExceeded {\n        result.Timeout = true\n        err = &ExecutionError{\n            Type:    ExecutionErrorTimeout,\n            Message: \"command timed out\",\n        }\n    }\n    \n    if exitErr, ok := err.(*exec.ExitError); ok {\n        if status, ok := exitErr.Sys().(syscall.WaitStatus); ok {\n            if status.Signal() == syscall.SIGKILL {\n                result.OOMKilled = true\n                err = &ExecutionError{\n                    Type:    ExecutionErrorOOM,\n                    Message: \"process killed due to OOM\",\n                }\n            }\n        }\n        result.ExitCode = exitErr.ExitCode()\n    } else if err == nil {\n        result.ExitCode = 0\n    }\n    \n    return result, err\n}\n```\n\n### Resource Limit Enforcement\n\n```go\nfunc (l *ResourceLimits) Apply(cmd *exec.Cmd) error {\n    if cmd.SysProcAttr == nil {\n        cmd.SysProcAttr = &syscall.SysProcAttr{}\n    }\n    \n    // Set CPU limits via cgroups (Linux)\n    if l.MaxCPU > 0 {\n        // Use cpu.cfs_quota_us and cpu.cfs_period_us\n        // This requires cgroup setup\n    }\n    \n    // Set memory limits\n    if l.MaxMemory > 0 {\n        cmd.SysProcAttr.Setpgid = true\n        // Memory limits via setrlimit\n        syscall.Setrlimit(syscall.RLIMIT_AS, &syscall.Rlimit{\n            Cur: uint64(l.MaxMemory),\n            Max: uint64(l.MaxMemory),\n        })\n    }\n    \n    // Set process limits\n    if l.MaxProcesses > 0 {\n        syscall.Setrlimit(syscall.RLIMIT_NPROC, &syscall.Rlimit{\n            Cur: uint64(l.MaxProcesses),\n            Max: uint64(l.MaxProcesses),\n        })\n    }\n    \n    return nil\n}\n```\n\n### Security Validation\n\n```go\nfunc ValidateCommand(cmd *Command, opts *SecurityOptions) error {\n    // 1. Check if command path is in allowlist\n    if len(opts.AllowedCommands) > 0 {\n        allowed := false\n        for _, allowedCmd := range opts.AllowedCommands {\n            if cmd.Path == allowedCmd {\n                allowed = true\n                break\n            }\n        }\n        if !allowed {\n            return fmt.Errorf(\"command %q not in allowlist\", cmd.Path)\n        }\n    }\n    \n    // 2. Validate working directory\n    if cmd.Dir != \"\" && !IsPathSafe(cmd.Dir, opts.WorkDir) {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"working directory %q is outside workspace\", cmd.Dir)\n    }\n    \n    // 3. Check for path traversal in arguments\n    for _, arg := range cmd.Args {\n        if strings.Contains(arg, \"..\") {\n            return fmt.Errorf(\"argument %q contains path traversal\", arg)\n        }\n    }\n    \n    // 4. Validate environment variables\n    for _, env := range cmd.Env {\n        if strings.HasPrefix(env, \"LD_PRELOAD\") || strings.HasPrefix(env, \"LD_LIBRARY_PATH\") {\n            return fmt.Errorf(\"dangerous environment variable: %s\", env)\n        }\n    }\n    \n    return nil\n}\n\nfunc IsPathSafe(path, workDir string) bool {\n    absPath, err := filepath.Abs(path)\n    if err != nil {\n        return false\n    }\n    \n    absWorkDir, err := filepath.Abs(workDir)\n    if err != nil {\n        return false\n    }\n    \n    return strings.HasPrefix(absPath, absWorkDir)\n}\n```\n\n## Configuration\n\n### Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Required | Default | Notes |\n|----------|----------|---------|-------|\n| `PICOD_WORKDIR` | No | `/tmp/picod` | Base working directory |\n| `PICOD_DEFAULT_TIMEOUT` | No | `30s` | Default command timeout |\n| `PICOD_MAX_MEMORY` | No | `128Mi` | Default memory limit |\n| `PICOD_MAX_CPU` | No | `1.0` | Default CPU limit |\n| `PICOD_MAX_OUTPUT_SIZE` | No | `10MB` | Default output size limit |\n| `PICOD_MAX_PROCESSES` | No | `10` | Default process limit |\n\n### Example Configuration\n\n```go\nconfig := &Config{\n    WorkDir:        \"/tmp/picod\",\n    DefaultTimeout: 30 * time.Second,\n    MaxMemory:      128 * 1024 * 1024, // 128 MiB\n    MaxCPU:         1.0,\n    MaxOutputSize:  10 * 1024 * 1024, // 10 MiB\n    MaxProcesses:   10,\n}\n```\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n| Test | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `TestPicoD_Run_Success` | Basic command execution |\n| `TestPicoD_Run_Timeout` | Command exceeds timeout |\n| `TestPicoD_Run_OOM` | Command exceeds memory limit |\n| `TestPicoD_Run_Cancelled` | Context cancellation |\n| `TestPicoD_OutputCapture` | Stdout/stderr capture |\n| `TestPicoD_SecurityValidation` | Invalid commands rejected |\n| `TestPicoD_ResourceLimits_Validate` | Resource limit validation |\n| `TestPicoD_SecurityOpts_Validate` | Security options validation |\n| `TestPicoD_WithOptions` | Functional options pattern |\n| `TestPicoD_ExecutionErrorTypes` | Error type classification |\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n| Test | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `TestPicoD_Integration_FullLifecycle` | Full execution flow |\n| `TestPicoD_Integration_Concurrent` | Multiple concurrent commands |\n| `TestPicoD_Integration_ResourceLimits` | Verify limits are enforced |\n| `TestPicoD_Integration_Streaming` | Output streaming functionality |\n| `TestPicoD_Integration_SignalHandling` | Process signal handling |\n\n### Test Fixtures\n\n```go\n// mockOutputHandler implements OutputHandler for testing\ntype mockOutputHandler struct {\n    stdoutCalls [][]byte\n    stderrCalls [][]byte\n    completeCalled bool\n    lastResult *CommandResult\n}\n\nfunc (m *mockOutputHandler) OnStdout(data []byte) {\n    m.stdoutCalls = append(m.stdoutCalls, data)\n}\n\nfunc (m *mockOutputHandler) OnStderr(data []byte) {\n    m.stderrCalls = append(m.stderrCalls, data)\n}\n\nfunc (m *mockOutputHandler) OnComplete(result *CommandResult) {\n    m.completeCalled = true\n    m.lastResult = result\n}\n```\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `PicoD` struct implements all required methods\n- [ ] Resource limits are enforced (timeout, CPU, memory, output size)\n- [ ] Output capture works correctly (stdout, stderr, exit code)\n- [ ] Cancellation via context is supported\n- [ ] Security validations prevent dangerous operations\n- [ ] Streaming output is supported\n- [ ] All unit tests pass\n- [ ] Integration tests pass\n- [ ] Code coverage >= 80%\n- [ ] Documentation includes usage examples\n- [ ] Error types are properly classified and documented\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Package | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|\n| `context` | Command cancellation and timeouts |\n| `os/exec` | Command execution primitives |\n| `syscall` | Process management and signals |\n| `k8s.io/klog/v2` | Structured logging |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | SandboxInfo type definitions |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` | Type definitions |\n\n## Affected Components\n\n1. **Sandbox Manager** (`pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox/`): Will use PicoD for command execution within sandboxes\n2. **Workload Manager** (`pkg/workloadmanager/`): Will invoke PicoD APIs for job execution\n3. **Code Interpreter** (standalone daemon): Will use PicoD execution logic\n4. **Security Module**: Will configure security policies for command execution\n5. **Monitoring System**: Will collect metrics from command execution\n\n## References\n\n- AR-012: Sandbox Infrastructure\n- AR-013: Session Storage\n- AR-014: Valkey Storage\n- `code-execution/spec.md`: PicoD Specification\n- `code-execution/design.md`: PicoD Design\n- `deployment/client-go.md`: Kubernetes Client-Go\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/picod/design.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/picod/design.md","time":{"start":1775859025147,"end":1775859025164}}}}
